ayi'' || [[File:Turdus grayi Garita, Alajuela Costa Rica-10.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.inbio.ac.cr/es/biod/yiguirro.htm|title=16 de diciembre: Declaraci\u00f3n del yig\u00fcirro como ave nacional de Costa Rica|publisher=|access-date=22 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529231434/http://www.inbio.ac.cr/es/biod/yiguirro.htm|archive-date=29 May 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[White-tailed deer]] ''(national animal)''||''Odocoileus virginianus'' || [[File:White-tailed deer.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.inbio.ac.cr/inbio/?p=296|title=El Venado Cola Blanca, S\u00edmbolo Nacional de la Fauna Silvestre|access-date=2015-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150515144544/http://blog.inbio.ac.cr/inbio/?p=296|archive-date=2015-05-15|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[West Indian manatee]] ''(national aquatic animal)'' ||''Trichechus manatus'' || [[File:Manatee with calf.PD - colour corrected.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.qcostarica.com/2014/07/30/manatee-now-costa-ricas-new-national-symbol/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140914050319/http://www.qcostarica.com/2014/07/30/manatee-now-costa-ricas-new-national-symbol/|title=Manatee Now Costa Rica's New National Symbol|archivedate=14 September 2014|work=QCOSTARICA}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{CRO}} || [[Pine marten]] ||''Martes martes'' || [[File:Martes martes, Clunes, Scotland 4.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"croatia\">{{cite book |last=Bousfield |first=Jonathan |title=Croatia |url=https://books.google.com/?id=UxSnm-mUp40C&pg=PA72&dq=croatian+national+animal#v=onepage&q=croatian%20national%20animal&f=false |accessdate=4 July 2013 |year=2003 |publisher=Rough Guides |isbn=978-1843530848 |page=72}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/ten-unusual-national-animals-rival-unicorn-180952804/?no-ist |title=Ten Unusual National Animals That Rival the Unicorn-8 of 10 |publisher=smithsonianmag.com |accessdate=2014-10-03}}</ref>\n|-\