om/nationalsymbols/national-animal-of-lebanon/|title=National Animal of Lebanon|date=2017-05-12|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Phoenix (mythology)|Phoenix]] ''(national bird)''\n| style=\"background:#ccc;\" |'''Mythical'''\n|[[File:Phoenix-Fabelwesen.jpg|alt=|right|150x150px]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://targetstudy.com/qna/what-are-the-national-symbols-of-lebanon.html|title=What are the National Symbols of Lebanon?|website=targetstudy.com|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{LBY}} || [[Lion]] || ''Panthera leo'' || [[File:Lion d'Afrique.jpg|150px]] || <ref name=\"Good\"/>\n|-\n|{{LIT}} || [[White stork]] ||''Ciconia ciconia''||[[File:WhiteStorkGaulsh02.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"Lithuania\">{{cite web|url=http://en.strasbourg-europe.eu/lithuania,13812,en.html|title=Lithuania|author=|work=Understanding the European Union :Member States|publisher=Centre d'Information sur les Institutions Europ\u00e9ennes (CIIE)|accessdate=2011-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720173110/http://en.strasbourg-europe.eu/lithuania,13812,en.html|archive-date=20 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{LUX}} || [[Lion]] || ''Panthera leo'' || [[File:Lion d'Afrique.jpg|150px]] || <ref name=\"Good\"/>\n|-\n| {{MKD}} || [[Lion]] ''(in [[Coat of arms of the Republic of Macedonia#Historical coats of arms|Macedonian heraldry]])'' ||''Panthera leo''||[[File:Macedonian Lion - Goce Delcev Bridge.JPG|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofmacedonia.org/Macedoniansymbols/MacedonianLion.html |title=History of Macedonia |publisher=History of Macedonia |accessdate=2013-08-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{MDG}} || [[Zebu]] ''(in [[Seal of Madagascar|Malagasy heraldry]]) ||''Bos primigenius indicus'' ||[[File:Z\u00e9bu.JPG|150px]] ||<ref>[https://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/africa/madagascar/mgsymbols.htm#page Symbols of Madagascar]</ref>\n|-\n| [[Ring-tailed lemur]] ''(national animal)'' ||''Lemur catta'' || [[File:Lemur catta 001.jpg|150p