stine adopts sunbird as emblem for exported goods|last=Qais|first=Abu Samra|date=September 18, 2018|work=[[Anadolu Agency]]|access-date=October 4, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{PAN}} || [[Harpy eagle]] ||''Harpia harpyja'' ||[[File:Harpia harpyja 001 800.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"6 Extremely Rare National Animals\"/>\n|-\n|{{PNG}} || [[Dugong]] ''(national marine mammal)'' ||''Dugong dugon'' ||[[File:Dugong Marsa Alam.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Hudson |first1=Brydget E.T. |year=1981 |title=Interview and Aerial Survey Data in Relation to Resource Management of the Dugong in Manus Province, Papua New Guinea  |journal=Bulletin of Marine Science |volume=31 |issue=3 |pages=662\u2013672 |url=http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/umrsmas/bullmar/1981/00000031/00000003/art00018 |accessdate=4 July 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{PER}} || [[Vicu\u00f1a]] ''(national animal)'' ||''Vicugna vicugna'' ||[[File:Vicunacrop.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/ten-unusual-national-animals-rival-unicorn-180952804/?no-ist |title=Ten Unusual National Animals That Rival the Unicorn-9 of 10 |publisher=smithsonianmag.com |accessdate=2014-10-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{PHL}}\n|[[Philippine eagle]] ''(national bird)''||''Pithecophaga jefferyi''||[[File:Sir Arny(Philippine Eagle).jpg|150px]]||<ref name=\"phsymeagle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.ph/1995/07/04/proclamation-no-615-s-1995/ |title=Proclamation No. 615, s. 1995 |publisher=gov.ph|accessdate=2012-08-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |{{POL}} || [[White-tailed eagle]] ''(national bird)''||''Haliaeetus albicilla'' || [[File:White-tailed Eagle Head detail.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://birds.poland.pl/directory/gallery%2CWhite-tailed_Eagle_%28Haliaeetus_albicilla%29%2Cgid%2C236008%2Ccid%2C923.htm |title=Polish Birds Directory: White-tailed Eagle (Haliaeetus albicilla) |publisher=birds.poland.pl |accessdate=2016-10-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080616044037/http://birds.poland.pl/directory/gallery%2CWhite-tailed_Eagle_%28Haliaeetus_albicilla%29%2Cgid%2C236008%2Ccid%2C923.htm |archivedate=16 June 2008 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://info-poland.buffalo.edu/classroom/eagle.html |title=symbols of Poland: The White Eagle |publisher=buffalo.edu |accessdate=2016-10-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010162805/http://info-poland.buffalo.edu/classroom/eagle.html |archivedate=10 October 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[White stork]] ''(national bird)''||''Ciconia ciconia'' || [[File:Ciconia ciconia - 01.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenews.pl/1/9/Artykul/25191,Poland-salutes-the-white-stork|title=Poland salutes the white stork|publisher=thenews.pl|accessdate=2016-10-10|author=}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[European bison]] ''(national animal)''||''Bison bonasus'' ||[[File:European Bison.JPG|150x150px]]||<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2011/apr/09/poland-wildlifeholidays|title=Primeval Poland: where the bison roam|publisher=theguardian.com|accessdate=2016-10-10|author=Jon Eldridge}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://allaboutbison.com/bison-world-news/europe/poland/|title=Poland|publisher=allaboutbison.com|accessdate=2016-10-10|author=}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{POR}} || [[Rooster of Barcelos]] ||style=\"background:#ccc;\"|'''Mythical''' || [[File:PA2900302 galo emiliarocha medio.jpg|sans_cadre|150px]]||<ref name=Po1>{{cite web|url=https://www.reference.com/geography/national-animal-portugal-a2c63c3800b560c2|website=www.reference.com|title=What is the national animal of Portugal?|access-date=22 October 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181214061538/https://www.reference.com/geography/national-animal-portugal-a2c63c3800b560c2|archive-date=14 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Iberian Wolf]] || ''Canis lupus signatus''||[[File:Canis lupus signatus (Kerkrade Zoo) 20.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=Po1/>\n|-\n|{{QAT}} || [[Arabian oryx]]||''Oryx leucoryx'' || [[File:Arabian oryx (oryx leucoryx).jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"Orr2008\">{{cite book|author=Tamra Orr|title=Qatar|url=https://archive.org/details/qatar0000orrt|url-access=registration|accessdate=30 July 2011|date=30 June 2008|publisher=Marshall Cavendish|isbn=978-0-7614-2566-3|page=[https://archive.org/details/qatar0000orrt/page/13 13]}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{ROM}} || [[Lynx]] ||''Lynx lynx'' || [[File:Lynx lynx poing.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.9am.ro/top/Social/243039/sapte-simboluri-nationale-mai-putin-cunoscute-romania/2/Animalul-national-Rasul.html|title=Animalul national - Rasul - Sapte simboluri nationale ale Romaniei mai putin cunoscute|work=9AM}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | {{RUS}} || [[Eurasian brown bear]] ''(national animal)'' ||''Ursus arctos arctos'' || [[File:European Brown Bear.jpg|150px]] || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.beavertonoregon.gov/DocumentCenter/Home/View/1197 |title=Birobidjan, Russia Beaverton's sister city since 1990 |publisher=The City of Beaverton|accessdate=2017-01-23}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Double-headed eagle]] ''(Traditional Coat of Arms)'' ||style=\"background:#ccc;\"|'''Mythical''' || [[File:Lesser Coat of Arms of Russian Empire.svg|150px]] || <ref>{{cite web |last1=Yergorov |first1=Oleg |title=Why is the double-headed eagle Russia's national symbol? |url=https://www.rbth.com/history/327634-why-is-double-headed-eagle-a-symbol-of-russia |website=rbth.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{RWA}} || [[Leopard]] ||''Panthera pardus''||[[File:Leopard africa.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/africa/rwanda/etsymbols.htm |title=Rwanda State Symbols, Song, Flag, and More |publisher=worldatlas.com|accessdate=2013-03-21}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{VCT}} || [[Saint Vincent amazon]] ||''Amazona guildingii'' ||[[File:Amazona guildingii -Botanical Gardens -Kingstown -Saint Vincent-8a-4c.jpg|150px]]||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foreign.gov.vc/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=91&Itemid=134|title=The National Bird|publisher=foreign.go