a/iran/irsymbols.htm|title=Iran National Symbols, Song, Flags and More - Worldatlas.com|website=www.worldatlas.com|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan = \"2\"|{{IRQ}}\n|[[Chukar partridge]]\n| ''Alectoris chukar''\n| [[File:Alectoris-chukar-001.jpg|150px]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/asia/iraq/iqsymbols.htm|title=Iraq|work=worldatlas.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Wild goat|Goat]] <br /> ({{Flagicon image|Flag of Kurdistan.svg}} [[Iraqi Kurdistan|KRG]])\n| ''Capra aegagrus''\n| [[File:Bezoarziege.jpg|150px]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kurdistanica.com/?q=node/193|title=The National Goat|work=kurdistanica.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{IRL}}\n|[[Red deer]] || ''Cervus elaphus'' || [[File:Cervus_elaphus_Luc_Viatour_6.jpg|169x169px]]||<ref>{{cite web|title=Irish National Animal|url=https://einfon.com/nationalsymbols/national-animal-of-ireland/|publisher=Country glossary|accessdate=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{ISR}}\n| [[Hoopoe]] ''(national bird)'' ||''Upupa epops'' ||[[File:Upupa epops (Ramat Gan)002.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"globalpost.com\" />\n|-\n|{{CIV}} || [[African elephant]] || ''Loxodonta'' || [[File:Elephant_near_ndutu.jpg|160px]]||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/africa/cotedivoire/cisymbols.htm|title=Cote D'ivoire State Symbols, Song, Flags and More - Worldatlas.com|website=www.worldatlas.com|access-date=2019-12-28}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{JAM}} || [[Red-billed streamertail]] ||''Trochilus polytmus'' ||[[File:Red-billed Streamertail 2506104129.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"jamsym\">{{cite web\n |url=http://www.jis.gov.jm/special_sections/This%20Is%20Jamaica/symbols.html \n |title=National Symbols of Jamaica \n |publisher=jis.gov.jm \n |accessdate=2011-12-02 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060619153047/http://www.jis.gov.jm/special_sections/This%20Is%20Jamaica/symbols.html \n |archivedate=19 June 2006 \n}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{JPN}} || [[Green pheasant]] ''(national bird)''  ||''Phasianus versicolor'' || [[File:Phasianus versicolor in field.JPG|150px]] || <ref name=\"jpnsymbrd\">{{cite web|url=http://sawacon.org/appeal/?p=1108|title=National Bird|accessdate=2015-03-14|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402105830/http://sawacon.org/appeal/?p=1108|archivedate=2 April 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Common carp|Carp]] ''(national fish)'' ||''Cyprinus carpio'' ||[[File:Koi at Japanese Garden - UH Manoa (5674161714-c).jpg|150px]] ||  <ref name=\"jpnsymfsh\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hanmoto.com/diary/2004/11/02/196/ |trans-title= Do you know \"Japanese fish\"? |language=ja |script-title=ja:\u65e5\u672c\u306e\u300c\u56fd\u9b5a\u300d\u3092\u3054\u5b58\u77e5\u3067\u3059\u304b\uff1f |accessdate=2015-03-14 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402090437/http://www.hanmoto.com/diary/2004/11/02/196/ |archivedate=2 April 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{KEN}} || [[Lion]] || ''Panthera leo'' || [[File:Lion d'Afrique.jpg|150px]] || <ref name=\"Good\">{{Cite journal|last=Good|first=Caroline|last2=Burnham|first2=Dawn|last3=Macdonald|first3=David|last4=Good|first4=Caroline|last5=Burnham|first5=Dawn|last6=Macdonald|first6=David W.|date=20 July 2017|title=A Cultural Conscience for Conservation|journal=Animals|language=en|volume=7|issue=12|pages=52|doi=10.3390/ani7070052|pmid=28726725|pmc=5532567}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{LAT}} || [[White wagtail]] ''(national bird)'' ||''Motacilla alba'' ||[[File:White-Wagtail.jpg|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|website=10,000 Birds|url=http://10000birds.com/what-is-the-national-bird-of-latvia.htm|title=What is the national bird of Latvia?|author=Corey|date=15 April 2011|accessdate=12 April 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Latvia Symbols\">{{cite web|website=Latvia.eu|url=http://www.latvia.eu/key-facts/symbols|title=Symbols|accessdate=12 April 2016|date=2016}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Adalia bipunctata|Two-spotted ladybird]] ''(national insect)'' ||''Adalia bipunctata''||[[File:Coccinellidae - Adalia bipunctata.JPG|150px]] ||<ref name=\"Latvia Symbols\"/>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{Flag|Lebanon}}\n|[[Striped hyena|Striped Hyena]] ''(national animal)''\n|''Hyaena hyaena''\n|[[File:Striped_Hyena_(Hyaena_hyaena).jpg|alt=|150x150px]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://einfon.com/nationalsymbols/national-animal-of-lebanon/|title=National Animal of Lebanon|date=2017-05-12|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Phoenix (mythology)|Phoenix]] ''(national bird)''\n| style=\"background:#ccc;\" |'''Mythical'''\n|[[File:Phoenix-Fabelwesen.jpg|alt=|right|150x150px]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://targetstudy.com/qna/what-are-the-national-symbols-of-lebanon.html|title=What are the National Symbols of Lebanon?|website=targetstudy.com|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{LBY}} || [[Lion]] || ''Panthera leo'' || [[File:Lion d'Afrique.jpg|150px]] || <ref name=\"Good\"/>\n|-\n|{{LIT}} || [[White stork]] ||''Ciconia ciconia''||[[File:WhiteStorkGaulsh02.jpg|150px]] ||<ref name=\"Lithuania\">{{cite web|url=http://en.strasbourg-europe.eu/lithuania,13812,en.html|title=Lithuania|author=|work=Understanding the European Union :Member States|publisher=Centre d'Information sur les Institutions Europ\u00e9ennes (CIIE)|accessdate=2011-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720173110/http://en.strasbourg-europe.eu/lithuania,13812,en.html|archive-date=20 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{LUX}} || [[Lion]] || ''Panthera leo'' || [[File:Lion d'Afrique.jpg|150px]] || <ref name=\"Good\"/>\n|-\n| {{MKD}} || [[Lion]] ''(in [[Coat of arms of the Republic of Macedonia#Historical coats of arms|Macedonian heraldry]])'' ||''Panthera leo''||[[File:Macedonian Lion - Goce Delcev Bridge.JPG|150px]] ||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.historyofmacedonia.org/Macedoniansymbols/MacedonianLion.html |title=History of Macedonia |publisher=History of Macedonia |accessdate=2013-08-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |{{MDG}} || [[Zebu]] ''(in [[Seal of Madagascar|Malagasy heraldry]]) ||''Bos primigenius i